# NAME

mwplight\ --\ the light preprocessor for megawave

# SYNOPSYS

**mwplight** \[ options \] modulesource  
**mwplight** \[ **-vh?** \]

# DESCRIPTION

**mwplight** parses a formatted module file for megawave, extracts
  information from the megawave header, and produces various files for
  a latter library or document compilation.

# OPTIONS

The name of the module source file are required. "-" can be used for
standard input/output.

-a, -\-afile *filename*
:	name of the A-file to write (main function of the run-time)

-m, -\-mfile *filename*
:	name of the M-file to write (source of the modified module)

-t, -\-tfile *filename*
:	name of the T-file to write (source of the module documentation)

-i, -\-ifile *filename*
:	name of the N-file to write (greoup and name of the module)

-n, -\-nfile *filename*
:	name of the I-file to write (interface file for an interpretor)

-g, -\-group *groupname*
:	group the module belongs to (defaults to "unknown")

-d, -\-debug
:	debug flag

-v, -\-version
:	print the version information

-h, -?, -\-help
:	print a short usage help

# ENVIRONMENT

Unlike previous versions, **mwplight** doesn't use any environment
variable; you must provide the full (absolute or relative) path to the
files.

# EXAMPLES

mwplight -a foo_a.c -m foo_m.c -t foo.tex -g bar foo.c

# SEE ALSO

**megawave(1)**, **libmw(3)**, **megawave-modules(1)**
